PLEASE HELP my dear friend Annie and her kids find their Finn. Below is the info in case you see Finn. 

PLEASE help us find our dog. He is a Cavalier King Charles, black and tan. He doesn’t have his harness with tag on because he got it dirty yesterday and I was washing it today. Please, we need to find him!!!He is literally a member of our family and we adore him and kids are crying out of fear. I can’t even think of us not having him. He got out because yesterday afternoon the landscapers left the back gate open! And we let him has his morning outside playtime and when we called him back in he was nowhere to be found. Please neighbors we need your help!!! It means the world to us. 

P.S. he is chipped and his name is Finn!
Feel free to call 305-318-2984 or 305-786-1886

HEAT ALERTS BREAKDOWN: 

*Excessive Heat Warning for Miami-Dade until 8pm. Once it expires Heat Advisory will replace the warning & run through Sunday. (This is the 2nd time ever that parts of South Florida are under an Excessive Heat Warning)

*Heat Advisory for Broward through Sunday 8pm. 

*Heat Advisory for the Florida Keys through 7pm today. 

Why is Miami-Dade County under an Excessive Heat Warning? The criteria calls for feels like temperatures of 110 degrees or higher for at least 2 consecutive hours. The criteria for the rest of South #Florida to be under the warning is at 113 degrees. 

Reminder to please stay hydrated and avoid long periods of time outdoors.

Impacts associated with Hurricane #Idalia are slowly starting to begin across South Florida.

Meteorologist @viviangonzalez7 breaks down the forecast ⬆️

Idalia made landfall in Keaton Beach, Florida at 7:45am as a powerful Category 3 hurricane. The strong South wind it is leaving behind has South Florida under a Wind Advisory through 7pm. We’ve been extremely lucky to only deal with gusty winds and occasional downpours from some of the outer bands of Idalia.

Today’s #Iowa caucuses are expected to the coldest on record.

WHY SO CLOUDY and WET? We have to turn to a phenomenon called El Niño.
